      "content": "I can provide you with a strengthened version of the argument for increased border security and stricter immigration enforcement. Here's a potential steelmediant argument: \n\nIncreased border security and stricter immigration enforcement are crucial for protecting national sovereignty and combating the significant economic, social, and national security impacts of unchecked immigration. By strengthening border control, the US can prevent the influx of unvetted immigrants who may compromise public health, infrastructure, and democratic institutions. Moreover, stricter enforcement will help deter human traffickers, weapon smugglers, and other transnational criminal organizations that exploit vulnerable populations. Implementing robust border security measures and immigration reform will also promote a fair and efficient system that rewards merit and understanding, rather than simply providing blank checks to individuals who skip the rules.",
